    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix signal mask handling in UE process signal handler setup\n\n### Summary\nThe NAS UE process signal handler setup contained a hardcoded list of signals that were unblocked during signal handling. This made the code unclear and maintenance-prone as it wasn't obvious why those specific signals were chosen.\n\nThe hardcoded approach also created inconsistent behavior where signals not in the hardcoded list would remain blocked even when handlers were set up for them.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/NAS/UE/UEprocess.c`: Replaced hardcoded signal unblocking with dynamic unblocking of the signal being handled\n- Updated function documentation to reflect the change in behavior\n\n### Reproduction\nUnder certain timing conditions, when the UE process receives a signal not in the hardcoded list (like SIGUSR1), the signal handler would not execute properly due to the signal remaining blocked. This could lead to delayed or missed signal processing, particularly noticeable during graceful shutdown sequences when external processes send termination signals to the UE process.\n"
}